Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Place 2 tbsp @butter{2%tbsp} in a small #microwave-safe bowl{}; set aside to soften (you'll use it in step 4). Wash and dry produce.

Core, deseed, and dice @Poblano Pepper{1}(deseeded and diced into ¼-inch pieces) into ¼-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and finely dice @Shallot{1}(peeled and finely diced) half the shallot (all for 4). Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce}(diced into ½-inch pieces) into ½-inch pieces. Drain and rinse @Corn{13.4%ounce}.

In a #pot{}, heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tsp} over medium-high heat. Add @Shrimp{10%ounce} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until opaque and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, combine softened @butter{4%tbsp}, @OLD BAY® Seasoning{¼%tsp}, and @Sugar{¼%tsp} until smooth. (For 4 servings, use ½ tsp Old Bay and ½ tsp sugar.) (TIP: If the butter is still cold, microwave for 10 seconds to soften.) Taste and add more Old Bay Seasoning if desired.

Halve @Demi-Baguette{1} lengthwise; spread cut sides with Old Bay butter. Place, cut sides up, on a #baking sheet{}.

Toast on top rack until golden, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Pour @Milk{6.75%oz} and @Flour{1%tbsp} into the pot, then stir milk into pot a splash at a time until fully incorporated.

Stir in 1 1/2 cups water (2 1/2 cups for 4 servings).

Add potatoes, @Veggie Stock Concentrate{2}, and half the @OLD BAY® Seasoning{1%unit} (you'll use more in the next step). Bring to a boil and cook, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are very tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> TIP: To test, pierce one piece with a fork—it should go through easily.

Once potatoes are tender, reduce heat to low and mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} to desired consistency.

> TIP: We recommend mashing until almost smooth, leaving a few small potato pieces for texture.

Stir in @Cream Cheese{2%tbsp}, corn, and @Monterey Jack Cheese{¼%cup}(shredded) until fully incorporated and chowder is thick and creamy. If needed, stir in splashes of water until chowder reaches desired consistency (it will be very thick at this point). Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once cream cheese and Monterey Jack are fully incorporated, stir in shrimp.

Halve Old Bay toast on a diagonal if desired.

Divide chowder between #bowls{}. Garnish with @Sour Cream{2%tbsp}. Serve with Old Bay toast on the side.